profile_positions.description:
Manage Shell Aircraft’s Quality and HSSE Management System and drive continuous improvement in Quality and HSSE compliance and performance. This includes:
o	Core member of the  Shell Aircraft Senior Leadership Team, reporting to the VP Shell Aircraft.
o	Motivate, coach and encourage Shell Aircraft staff to champion the delivery of Quality and HSSE goals, providing resource support, tools and facilitation aids as appropriate.
o	Own the (Aircraft) Incident investigation process. Support Shell Investigate and Learn with aviation practices.
o	Manage Shell Aircraft’s overall audit program and monitor timely and appropriate follow-up on findings;
o	Act as Shell Aircraft’s focal point for Shell Group HSSE reporting requirements and interface activities;
o	Engagement with external organisations to develop Quality and HSSE improvements and implement best practices.

Provide independent assurance to Accountable Manager Corporate Aviation for airworthiness and operations of the corporate fleet) that the applicable regulatory requirements and standards regarding aircraft maintenance and operations are being met. This includes:
o Report directly to the Accountable Manager for matters related to continuing airworthiness management and quality assurance in both airworthiness and operations;
o Act as the focal point for implementation and compliance with EASA Part NCC and OTARS regulations and IS-BAO certification;
o Manage the renewal of the relevant aircraft certificates and review and obtain regulatory approval for documents related to airworthiness;
o NPH Quality and Safety for the Dutch Civil Aviation Authority (P145) and Bermuda Civil Aviation Authority (AOC/M).
o Lead the development of Aviation SMS tools and processes, such as air transport model bowties,  improved reporting on aircraft operator audit findings and air transport incidents in support of Shell’s air transport activities.

Responsible for carrying out operational and technical audits and issue timely reports after approval by the Advisory Service Director or Senior Advisor. Ensuring that recommendations arising from audits are followed up, and where insufficient action has been taken to close safety-critical recommendations by the agreed target date, escalate the issue to the appropriate higher level. Ensuring that the principles of aviation safety management have been adopted by aircraft operators during the audit process, participation in incident and accident investigations, and providing timely and well judged professional aviation operational and technical advice appropriate to customer needs.

Key Accountabilities: 
• Acting as Focal Point for specific areas of expertise and various assigned countries;
 • Assisting the Operating Units to prepare competitive air support contracts that ensure high standards of safety and efficiency;
 • Supporting ShelI in the maintenance of its Corporate Quality and Safety Management System (SMS);
 • Providing specialist technical and contracting strategy advice to Operating Units and customers;
 • Convincing contractor at Senior Executive level to improve their operational and technical standards and safety management systems by adopting the principles of the Shell Group Aircraft SMS.
